1
00:00:17,320 --> 00:00:19,280
[Recording]

2
00:00:19,280 --> 00:00:20,280
Time flies,

3
00:00:20,730 --> 00:00:21,930
and the years slip by.

4
00:00:22,440 --> 00:00:24,700
We've known each other for ten years now.

5
00:00:25,190 --> 00:00:27,050
In this fleeting stretch of time,

6
00:00:27,680 --> 00:00:29,520
you've given me endless warmth

7
00:00:30,280 --> 00:00:33,280
and made my life so much better.

8
00:00:34,120 --> 00:00:34,920
Xia Xue,

9
00:00:35,880 --> 00:00:36,960
will you marry me?

10
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:30,730
[THE GUILTY]

11
00:02:31,150 --> 00:02:35,530
[Episode 3]

12
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:40,190
[Sancheng Financial Services]

13
00:02:40,630 --> 00:02:42,280
We turned Nanping

14
00:02:42,310 --> 00:02:44,030
upside down—

15
00:02:44,079 --> 00:02:45,650
hair salons,

16
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:47,280
mahjong parlors,

17
00:02:47,310 --> 00:02:49,090
docks, bus stations, hotels,

18
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:49,870
KTVs—

19
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:52,590
every corner.

20
00:02:52,630 --> 00:02:54,400
And still, we couldn't find Ma Derong.

21
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:56,130
Hello. Police. Is Lu Ming here?

22
00:03:05,730 --> 00:03:06,520
Have a seat.

23
00:03:14,390 --> 00:03:16,650
Who would want to be a lighthouse keeper?

24
00:03:17,020 --> 00:03:18,079
There's not a soul here.

25
00:03:18,079 --> 00:03:19,079
It's so desolate.

26
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:21,329
We'll know when we're up there.

27
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:28,340
Lin Hua, do you remember me?

28
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:30,480
Of course.

29
00:03:31,010 --> 00:03:32,040
Long time no see.

30
00:03:32,980 --> 00:03:34,850
It's been ten years, hasn't it?

31
00:03:34,870 --> 00:03:35,530
Have a seat.

32
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:37,510
Smoke?

33
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,690
No, thanks.

34
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:40,890
You're Officer Qin Wen.

35
00:03:41,060 --> 00:03:41,920
I remember you.

36
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:43,640
You have a good memory.

37
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:46,650
I'll get straight to the point.

38
00:03:46,710 --> 00:03:47,470
I'm here today

39
00:03:47,470 --> 00:03:48,400
mainly about

40
00:03:48,540 --> 00:03:50,210
a case involving Xia Xue.

41
00:03:50,430 --> 00:03:52,090
I have a few questions for you.

42
00:03:52,590 --> 00:03:54,360
Do you know that Xia Xue has a daughter

43
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:55,490
named Hou Shanshan?

44
00:03:57,540 --> 00:03:58,510
No.

45
00:03:59,410 --> 00:04:00,800
Hou Shanshan is missing.

46
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:01,630
Missing?

47
00:04:01,990 --> 00:04:04,290
You should go look for her,

48
00:04:04,530 --> 00:04:05,650
not me.

49
00:04:09,060 --> 00:04:11,940
Then you must have no idea

50
00:04:11,970 --> 00:04:14,030
who Hou Shanshan's father is, right?

51
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:17,649
Well, obviously. If she's a Hou,
her dad must be one, too.

52
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:20,529
Lin Hua,

53
00:04:20,930 --> 00:04:21,930
let me remind you.

54
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:22,870
This is no longer

55
00:04:22,870 --> 00:04:24,670
a simple child kidnapping case.

56
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:26,920
It now involves intentional homicide.

57
00:04:27,630 --> 00:04:30,340
Judging by Hou Shanshan's age,

58
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:33,190
Xia Xue would have still
been in a relationship with you

59
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:34,520
at the time of the birth.

60
00:04:37,390 --> 00:04:38,200
Officer Qin.

61
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:40,650
What does that mean?

62
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:43,040
You can't just say things like that.

63
00:04:45,270 --> 00:04:46,130
How about this?

64
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,310
You go ask Xia Xue.

65
00:04:47,310 --> 00:04:49,360
Whoever she names is the father,

66
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:51,020
but I'm not taking the fall for this.

67
00:04:51,020 --> 00:04:52,590
Why did you break up later?

68
00:05:04,050 --> 00:05:06,450
We were actually getting along quite well.

69
00:05:10,110 --> 00:05:12,770
But then, something happened
with her family.

70
00:05:18,870 --> 00:05:19,750
People change,

71
00:05:20,070 --> 00:05:20,800
you know.

72
00:05:21,660 --> 00:05:24,060
She wanted someone reliable,

73
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,380
someone with a career.

74
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:28,660
I understand that.

75
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:36,360
Xia Xue married a rich guy.

76
00:05:37,270 --> 00:05:38,310
And Lu Ming

77
00:05:38,630 --> 00:05:39,690
started a company.

78
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:41,900
I'm just a lighthouse keeper.

79
00:05:45,870 --> 00:05:47,159
You can see that.

80
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:50,070
Our lives don't intersect anymore.

81
00:05:50,070 --> 00:05:51,630
So what's there to contact?

82
00:06:03,430 --> 00:06:04,300
Lu Ming.

83
00:06:04,990 --> 00:06:07,270
I remember back then,

84
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:09,160
you were a student
at Huacheng University,

85
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:10,630
majoring in Law, right?

86
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:12,630
What made you change paths

87
00:06:12,630 --> 00:06:13,830
and do a job like this?

88
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:16,480
What's wrong with it?

89
00:06:16,850 --> 00:06:18,250
I'm just making a living.

90
00:06:18,510 --> 00:06:19,480
Besides,

91
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:21,210
this is a legitimate business.

92
00:06:22,970 --> 00:06:23,680
Don't get upset.

93
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:24,510
We aren't here today

94
00:06:24,510 --> 00:06:26,170
to investigate your business.

95
00:06:26,170 --> 00:06:28,440
We just want to ask about Hou Shanshan.

96
00:06:35,950 --> 00:06:36,750
Well, even if we're not

97
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:38,430
talking business,

98
00:06:38,430 --> 00:06:41,090
surely you won't deny us
a simple glass of water?

99
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:55,870
Here.

100
00:06:55,870 --> 00:06:56,470
Thank you.

101
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:57,360
Thanks.

102
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,940
You were pretty sharp.

103
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,960
Could Lu Ming have killed Wang Bingkun?

104
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:24,890
I don't know.

105
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:26,890
The silhouette looks like him.

106
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:27,390
Run a DNA test,

107
00:07:27,390 --> 00:07:28,430
and we'll know.

108
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:32,700
[Sancheng Financial Services]

109
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:50,800
Lin Hua.

110
00:07:51,310 --> 00:07:52,870
I think if you

111
00:07:52,870 --> 00:07:54,240
still consider them friends,

112
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,970
you'd better tell us the truth.

113
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:57,430
I will.

114
00:07:58,310 --> 00:07:59,240
That's the only way we can

115
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:01,100
help Xia Xue find her child faster

116
00:08:02,310 --> 00:08:04,040
and clear Lu Ming of suspicion.

117
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:06,630
What suspicion?

118
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:12,280
Lin Hua lied.

119
00:08:12,310 --> 00:08:14,330
He must still be in contact with them.

120
00:08:14,330 --> 00:08:15,450
And did you notice?

121
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:16,720
When we brought up

122
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:18,430
Lu Ming and Xia Xue,

123
00:08:18,430 --> 00:08:20,680
Lin Hua's reaction
was unnatural,

124
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:21,850
as if he was desperate
to hide some kind of truth.

125
00:08:21,850 --> 00:08:22,710
[Lin's Repairs]

126
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:24,730
And I discovered an important clue.

127
00:08:27,770 --> 00:08:30,480
Their statements
are surprisingly consistent.

128
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:34,210
They all avoided talking
about Hou Shanshan's biological father.

129
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:40,659
Let's head back to the Bureau.

130
00:08:40,659 --> 00:08:40,789
[Lin's Repairs]

131
00:08:40,789 --> 00:08:41,200
Yes.

132
00:09:07,620 --> 00:09:11,760
[1999]

133
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,080
Kai.

134
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:31,670
Guess what?

135
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:33,630
Xia Gang

136
00:09:34,030 --> 00:09:36,480
moved all the fire extinguishers
in the office.

137
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:38,320
Then find something else for him to do.

138
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,670
I'm way ahead of you.

139
00:09:40,510 --> 00:09:42,190
I made him copy down the...

140
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,630
vehicle entry and exit logs.

141
00:09:43,630 --> 00:09:45,360
He can't leave until he's done.

142
00:09:47,550 --> 00:09:48,350
What's wrong?

143
00:09:48,910 --> 00:09:50,510
You're still not satisfied?

144
00:09:51,390 --> 00:09:52,720
Did you deliver the car?

145
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:53,720
Yes.

146
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:57,200
How's the dealership doing lately?

147
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:58,920
Really well.

148
00:09:59,910 --> 00:10:02,840
Those cars we flipped
are selling really well.

149
00:10:03,270 --> 00:10:05,600
Of course, it's all because
of your reputation.

150
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:07,440
We've sold three this week.

151
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:09,120
If your dad knew
you were making money like this,

152
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:10,260
he'd be thrilled.

153
00:10:12,030 --> 00:10:13,270
You think my dad would be happy?

154
00:10:13,270 --> 00:10:14,600
Definitely.

155
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,800
It's yours now. I just bought it.

156
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:25,000
What have Xia Xue

157
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:25,250
and that college boy of hers been up to?

158
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:26,940
[Motorbike]

159
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:32,150
Kai.

160
00:10:33,510 --> 00:10:37,000
Do you have a thing for her?

161
00:10:38,570 --> 00:10:39,630
I was just kidding.

162
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:41,950
Gotta go. Tonight, Jinlong Food Stall.

163
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:52,910
Over there.

164
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:54,910
That's a lot of people.

165
00:10:54,910 --> 00:10:56,030
Of course.

166
00:10:56,270 --> 00:10:58,000
This tree's really something.

167
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:59,510
Many big bosses

168
00:10:59,510 --> 00:11:01,110
come here to pray every year.

169
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:02,790
So, when you returned to Nanping,

170
00:11:02,790 --> 00:11:03,840
we should have come here first

171
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:04,550
and prayed.

172
00:11:04,550 --> 00:11:05,200
Maybe then,

173
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,910
we wouldn't have had such bad luck.

174
00:11:06,910 --> 00:11:07,480
Yeah.

175
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:08,960
We should have listened to Lin Hua.

176
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:11,360
I didn't hear about it
a couple of years ago.

177
00:11:11,870 --> 00:11:12,330
Auntie.

178
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:14,150
Don't throw this. Give it to us.

179
00:11:14,150 --> 00:11:14,510
Right.

180
00:11:14,510 --> 00:11:15,240
Give it to us.

181
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:15,800
Lin Hua.

182
00:11:16,910 --> 00:11:18,360
Look, our offering
stands out from the rest.

183
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,200
When the gods see

184
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,360
how different we are,

185
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:22,360
they'll take care of our business first.

186
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:23,550
If it doesn't work, I'm coming for you.

187
00:11:23,550 --> 00:11:24,210
Okay, okay.

188
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,530
Gods, please bless

189
00:11:36,030 --> 00:11:38,910
Lu Ming and Xia Xue with a baby soon.

190
00:11:39,670 --> 00:11:42,000
If you're gonna pray,
pray for the three of us—

191
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:42,640
together.

192
00:11:43,330 --> 00:11:45,780
Then here's to everything going smoothly,

193
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,110
and to staying safe and sound.

194
00:11:47,110 --> 00:11:47,630
Okay.

195
00:11:47,630 --> 00:11:48,790
Smooth and safe.

196
00:11:58,910 --> 00:12:01,440
What are you wishing for?
It's taking so long.

197
00:12:01,870 --> 00:12:03,960
-Just having a heart-to-heart with him.
-Tell me. I’ll listen.

198
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:04,390
Forget it.

199
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:05,360
What's in your heart?

200
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:06,440
It won't work if I say it out loud.

201
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:08,670
Probably it is still about having a baby.

202
00:12:08,670 --> 00:12:09,440
You...

203
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,400
Don't talk nonsense.

204
00:12:12,550 --> 00:12:13,510
Seriously,

205
00:12:13,510 --> 00:12:14,600
what did you guys wish for?

206
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:15,200
I can't tell you.

207
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:16,600
Just a small wish.

208
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:30,790
Young Mr. Ma.

209
00:12:30,790 --> 00:12:31,990
What took you so long?

210
00:12:35,660 --> 00:12:37,390
Cook some noodles for me later.

211
00:12:44,410 --> 00:12:44,970
Dad.

212
00:12:48,150 --> 00:12:50,680
Didn't you say
you were coming back tomorrow?

213
00:12:54,730 --> 00:12:56,260
You've gained some weight.

214
00:12:58,360 --> 00:12:59,760
You're back early today.

215
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:02,670
It's the usual time.

216
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:04,300
Did you miss me?

217
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:06,900
I heard

218
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:08,410
you're looking for someone

219
00:13:08,410 --> 00:13:10,740
to deal with a policewoman at the station.

220
00:13:14,670 --> 00:13:15,790
Do you need my help?

221
00:13:18,790 --> 00:13:19,430
No.

222
00:13:19,790 --> 00:13:20,360
Have a seat.

223
00:13:20,360 --> 00:13:21,200
Sit.

224
00:13:24,550 --> 00:13:25,640
Here's my plan.

225
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:27,390
I'll start at her place...

226
00:13:27,390 --> 00:13:28,320
I'm warning you.

227
00:13:29,510 --> 00:13:30,970
Stay away from the police.

228
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:33,670
I've investigated her.

229
00:13:33,670 --> 00:13:37,200
-She has no background.
-Our company is in the middle of a reorg.

230
00:13:37,870 --> 00:13:39,130
Don't let your actions

231
00:13:39,790 --> 00:13:40,990
ruin the big picture.

232
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:44,920
Do you hear me?

233
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:46,970
Do you hear me?

234
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:49,150
Do you hear me?

235
00:13:49,150 --> 00:13:50,600
Yes, yes.

236
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:55,910
Go.

237
00:13:56,390 --> 00:13:57,250
Go to your room.

238
00:13:57,750 --> 00:13:58,610
There's a gift.

239
00:14:02,910 --> 00:14:05,170
We'll talk about the policewoman later.

240
00:14:07,710 --> 00:14:08,640
Where is it?

241
00:14:10,630 --> 00:14:13,200
Dad, I love you so much!

242
00:14:15,790 --> 00:14:18,200
All shifts and teams,
get your fire extinguishers.

243
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:20,000
Take them back and check them carefully.

244
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:22,600
If any are damaged, come back
and exchange them immediately.

245
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:23,000
Here.

246
00:14:28,210 --> 00:14:29,670
You're here, Young Mr. Ma.

247
00:14:31,780 --> 00:14:31,960
[Sign-in Log]

248
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:33,220
Should we get started?

249
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:35,000
Why don't you take your men
to check first?

250
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,260
I still need to see Qiu.

251
00:14:36,560 --> 00:14:38,200
[Ma Kai]

252
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:38,550
Okay.

253
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,880
You just take your men and check.

254
00:14:47,390 --> 00:14:48,750
Are these fire extinguishers new?

255
00:14:48,750 --> 00:14:49,350
Yes.

256
00:14:49,570 --> 00:14:52,570
Xia from the Security Department
just replaced them.

257
00:14:54,100 --> 00:14:55,290
They're so dirty,

258
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:56,920
and you call them new?

259
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:57,800
Young Mr. Ma.

260
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,460
New or old, they work the same.

261
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,130
Just replaced, huh?

262
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:12,200
Young Mr. Ma, what are you doing?

263
00:15:13,030 --> 00:15:13,960
These are all new.

264
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:14,820
Just replaced.

265
00:15:15,630 --> 00:15:16,890
None of your business.

266
00:15:24,220 --> 00:15:25,950
You can't use them now, can you?

267
00:15:29,710 --> 00:15:32,200
You said the fire equipment

268
00:15:32,240 --> 00:15:34,200
is Xia Gang's responsibility
from the Security Department, right?

269
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:35,200
Yes, Young Mr. Ma.

270
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,260
Handle this strictly.

271
00:15:39,390 --> 00:15:41,120
Don't be grinning all day long.

272
00:15:41,890 --> 00:15:43,020
Go on with the check.

273
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:44,850
What are you waiting for?

274
00:15:44,850 --> 00:15:45,980
Move them, quickly.

275
00:16:09,910 --> 00:16:13,390
Rose, rose, so fair and sweet.

276
00:16:13,390 --> 00:16:14,600
You sing terribly.

277
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:15,840
You sing then.

278
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:16,480
Go ahead.

279
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:17,200
You sing.

280
00:16:17,240 --> 00:16:18,240
I sing even worse.

281
00:16:32,550 --> 00:16:33,640
Alright.

282
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:41,960
What is this?

283
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:43,750
This is the DV

284
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:44,690
I borrowed from the shipyard.

285
00:16:44,690 --> 00:16:45,950
Why did you borrow a DV?

286
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:48,810
Of course we have to record
such an important day.

287
00:16:52,620 --> 00:16:53,990
Why is it important?

288
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:57,480
Today is Lin Hua's

289
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:58,840
